\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
\color blue
\lang bahasa
When I got my library card, that's when my life began.
 --Rita Mae Brown
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang bahasa
In this module we can enter the master file data that can be used as a master
 in bibliographic data entry.
 The data that can be defined in this Master File module is:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang bahasa
GMD General Material Designation – The physical form of the media item 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang bahasa
Publisher* – Publisher name
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang bahasa
Supplier – Supplier is a supplier of items being placed in the collection
 e.g a pareticular bookstore
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang bahasa
Statement of Responsibility – persons or bodies responsible for the the
 creation of the item
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang bahasa
Author* – author's name and the type of author (individual or group)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang bahasa
Subject* – the topic/subject, classification code, subject type, and authority
 files source.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
\align center

\lang bahasa
\begin_inset Float figure
placement H
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename image/master-subjec-new.png
	scale 65

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\lang bahasa
\begin_inset Caption

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\lang bahasa
Master File-Subject
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang bahasa
Location – location code and the name of the location where the item is
 placed
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang bahasa
Place – contains the place of publication
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang bahasa
Item Status – contains the status of the item (Repair, On Loan, Reserved).
 Each Item Status category contains the Item Status Code , Item Status Name
 and Rules.
 There are two options in Rules: No Loan Transaction (items can not be borrowed,
 eg digital collections) and Skipped by Take Stock (not contained in the
 process of the Stock Take)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang bahasa
Collection Type – the type of item collections owned by the library, for
 example: Textbook, Reference
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang bahasa
Doc.
 Language – the language used by the document.
 Eg: Indonesian, English, French, Javanese etc..
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang bahasa
Label – To provide specific information about the bibliographic item.
 labels can be defined in the Master File menu.
 By default Senayan has three labels: New Title, Favorite Title and Multimedia.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang bahasa
Frequency – contains the time/frequency of publications published ( for
 serial publications )
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\lang bahasa
* In addition to being entered through the Master Files, Publisher, Author
 and Subject data can also be entered when loading bibliographic data e.g
 MARC data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\lang bahasa
In Senayan3-Stable15/Matoa there are also new features grouped in Tools.
 These features include Orphaned Author and Orphaned Subject.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\lang bahasa
Both these features are used to refine the author/authors and subjects that
 are not used in the SLiMS database.
 When it has been filtered by clicking Orphaned Author or Orphaned Subject,
 a list of subjects or authors that are not used will appear.
 If you want to remove them, please select some or all, then Delete.
\end_layout

